The paper deals with generating descriptions of images using neural sequence models, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with CV. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for generating descriptions, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine translation techniques, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
